            , was again indicted for <rs id="t18280703-187-off928" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-off928" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-off928" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280703-187-cd929" type="crimeDate">20th of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-187-off928 t18280703-187-cd929"></join>, 4 printed bound books, value 20s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18280703-187-victim1065" type="victimName">
                  Thomas 
                  North
               <interp inst="t18280703-187-victim1065" type="surname" value="North"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-victim1065" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-victim1065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-187-off928 t18280703-187-victim1065"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS NORTH. I know these four books to be mine; they were in my shop this day three weeks.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Have you not said, that if the persons who came to your shop did not come to steal books, they might come to enable others to steal them? A. Yes, I have. I know you formerly were in the habit of buying and selling books.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-187-person1066">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PERRY
               <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1066" type="surname" value="PERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1066" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1066" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. These four books were pawned with me by the prisoner, on Monday afternoon, the 23d of June, in the name of John Edwards.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Are you sure of that? A. I am; Mr. Anderton is my servant - I know you by pawning books before; you wore a black coat - your hair was longer than it is now, but I know you well; I have not claimed any reward.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-187-person1067">
                  CHARLES 
                  THOROWGOOD
               <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1067" type="surname" value="THOROWGOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1067" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-187-person1067" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I found the duplicate of these four books on the prisoner's person - he gave it up to me.</p>
               <p>MR. NORTH. I offered a reward of 5l. about the books - Mr. Anderton, himself, called about it.</p>
               <p>The prisoner stated that he had purchased this duplicate of the same person.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280703-187-verdict930" type="verdictDescription">
